------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1330 | thelusiv | 2006-11-09 23:30:35 -0800 (Thu, 09 Nov 2006) | 2 lines

Set up a way for gas to be restricted when using button controls with auto shifting. This avoids over-revving the engine when the gas button is held down and an automatic shift takes place.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1329 | thelusiv | 2006-11-09 22:34:18 -0800 (Thu, 09 Nov 2006) | 7 lines

A few updates to the automatic transmission mode:
* Changed menu name of option from "AutoTrans" to "AutoShift"
* Made autoclutch always on if autotrans option is on
* Instead of directly calling shift_up and shift_down, shifting now runs the action "disengage_shift_[up/down]"
* Implemented a function to find an ideal point to down shift, using rookie1's suggested algorithm
* one little change to the algorithm, was to make it shift down at a slightly lower RPM than the "optimal" shift point - to avoid shifting up, then immediately back down, and up again, etc.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
