------------------------------------------------------------------------
r361 | thelusiv | 2005-10-03 23:59:40 -0700 (Mon, 03 Oct 2005) | 2 lines

Added a command line option to change the data directory in the default VDrift.config (the one in /usr/...). Running "vdrift -defaultdatadir /path/to/vdrift/data" will fix this. This will be used by the installer script for the Linux binary package to make sure that VDrift doesn't lose its data.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r360 | thelusiv | 2005-10-03 22:43:24 -0700 (Mon, 03 Oct 2005) | 2 lines

Implemented the ability for VDrift to easily change the data directory using a runtime flag. Now, running "vdrift -datadir /path/to/vdrift/data" will do this.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
