r3 | joevenzon | 2005-07-20 20:25:32 -0700 (Wed, 20 Jul 2005) | 3 lines

Fixed the mustang's mass and drivetrain inertia.


------------------------------------------------------------------------
r2 | joevenzon | 2005-07-20 18:11:16 -0700 (Wed, 20 Jul 2005) | 1 line

Autotools updated by Jens Granseuer, you can now do ./configure --with-fmod if you want fmod, or a plain configure without options for OpenAL.  Also fixed remaining replay crashes.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r1 | thelusiv | 2005-07-19 23:31:32 -0700 (Tue, 19 Jul 2005) | 2 lines

Initial import of 2005-07-18 (OpenAL) release

------------------------------------------------------------------------

11-2-2005
Updated/fixed a ton of stuff, added mouse driving, sound volume, torque curves, new car format, new config file, in-car camera bump, flatter tracks, swappable car parts, autoclutch, OS X support, and much more.

10-2-2005
Added networked multiplayer, moved from autotools to SCons, made installable system-wide, settings directory /home/user/.vdrift, new detail options

9-1-2005
Added a foliage system, added trees, added objects, added an '88 porche, added a new track, re-did the terrain for nurburgring.

8-2-2005
Added a logo screen, revamped the menu background, added a New Game menu, added track selection and a new track, added car paint colors (up/down on the car select screen), improved the replay code by adding re-syncing every second (in preparation for networked multiplayer) -- this also makes replays much more robust when they are shared with other people.

7-25-2005
Revamped the tire friction code, tweaked the cars, added a timer graphic.

7-18-2005
Added Chris' S2000, car selection menu, interior models, restructured data/cars, seem to have fixed crash when turning into skewed corners, fixed keyboard control bugs.

7-10-2005
Added skew from the latest vamos release so sharp corners look correct, framerate and HUD can now be toggled on/off, replay improvements, and hopefully the packaging of FMOD will eliminate sound problems (you may need to copy the FMOD lib from VDrift/lib to /usr/lib and run ldconfig).

7-7-2005
Updated menu graphics, updated moon graphic, switched to FMOD for sound, added brake lights, added trimming to the world reset, added replay versioning, and reduced the size of replay files.

6-25-2005
Texture formats are now auto-detected. New menus from Chris Guirl. Enhanced performance to compensate for the loss of performance in the last release. Added a joystick deadzone option. Added an in-car view that gets its position from the car's xml file. Fixed a lingering bug with replay/lap time interaction. Added stars and a moon. Added two external camera views, improved the chase view. Fixed a bug in the tachometer texture. With the camera in orbit mode, you can now zoom in and out with the left and right mouse buttons, respectively. Fixed a bug that was causing fuel and speedo needles to not line up correctly. Fixed a bug caused by the way the car's shadow was drawn. Adjusted particle code to clip to the car (so smoke doesn't drift through it -- as much). Added an analog clutch.

6-17-2005
Fixed replay pausing/screenshot/trackshot bugs. Fixed FreeCam camera mode. Made the car a lot like a Mustang (which doesn't drift much at all... hopefully I'll add a better car next release). Make the tachometer dynamically generated based on engine parameters. Added elevation to the surface where the track is. This incurred a big performance penalty, so I had to bump down the terrain detail to compensate.

6-12-2005
Added a setting for control touchiness compensation in the Control Options menu. Camera mode is now saved. Added a menu option for refueling. Added replay functionality (more refinements to come). Updated HUD graphics from Chris Guirl. New car model from Teemu Haapoja.

6-9-2005
Created an in-game interface for control editing. Added code to make the steering less touchy for joysticks (so make sure you select Wheel in Control Options on the Main Menu to deactivate this if you have a wheel). A couple small bugs were fixed.

6-4-2005
Added a fuel gauge. Added lap timing. Created an in-game menu for changing resolution & toggling fullscreen. Press F12 to get into the menu.

5-31-2005
Fixed a steering bug. Fixed a few sound bugs.

5-29-2005
Improved build files that now check for required libraries, hopefully fixed some build issues, added verbose initialization switch, changed how transparent glass is handled, cleaned out the runtime folder.

5-28-2005
Sound via OpenAL, improved control realism.

5-3-2005
Improved car rendering, smaller terrain file size.

4-23-2005
More small fixes, impoved terrain texturing and lighting.

4-9-2005
Tiny bug fixes, added a joystick info mode to help you modify the controls file (lists/controls) for you joystick (press j), and the first release that compiles without modification on windows and linux.

4-8-2005
Numerous small bug fixes, a new track, and the first windows release.

4-2-2005
Fixed texture bugs, added shadows, added a particle system for tire smoke, sped up car rendering.

4-1-2005
Added a terrain engine, tweaked the track code, added simple reflections to the car. Also changed some things to get it to compile better across more platforms.

3-29-2005
Initial release. New model format, new font engine, new camera engine, other small tweaks.
